<HEADLINE> Four Tons of Marijuana Seized in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian police seized a
total of 4,146 kilograms of marijuana Friday at the port of
Sihanoukville, Rasmei Kampuchea Daily reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It was the largest haul of marijuana seized by Cambodian police
this year and the case was under investigation, the newspaper
said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the marijuana, loaded in a container with
17 tons of soybean, was slated to be shipped to Britain.
</P>
<P>
Illegal cultivation and trafficking of marijuana have been
rampant in Cambodia's central provinces in recent years, including
Kandal province.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia is seen by traffickers as an ideal spot for cannabis
production and a transshipment point for other narcotics. The
Royal Government of Cambodia is taking some drastic measures to
crack down on illegal cultivation, production and trafficking of
the drugs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
