<HEADLINE> Clinton Seeks Gun Control Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- U. S. President Bill Clinton
is seeking gun-control legislation following Tuesday's tragic school
shooting which killed 15 people.
</P>
<P>
The president, in his weekly radio address Saturday,
requests the Congress to approve 12 million dollars for
emergency teams to help communities respond when tragedy occurs.
</P>
<P>
He also requests gun-control regislation focusing on keeping
guns out of the hands of juveniles.
</P>
<P>
"The government must take responsibility," Clinton said,"We
must do more to prevent violence in our schools."
</P>
<P>
He said his Safe Schools Bill would crack down on gun shows
and illegal gun trafficking, prohibit "violent juveniles" from
being able to buy guns and close "the loophole that lets juveniles
own assault rifles".  
</P>
</TEXT>
