<HEADLINE> School Shootings Shows Something Wrong in America: Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Seventy-nine percent of
American people said the tragic school shooting shows something
seriously wrong in the country today, according to a poll jointly
taken by CNN, USA Today and Gallup Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Another poll, taken by CBS, said 80 percent expect more
shootings like the attacks at a Colorado high school to occur
elsewhere in the country over the next year or so.
</P>
<P>
As many as 15 people, including the two teenage killers, were
killed Tuesday in Colorado in the worst school shooting in
American history.
</P>
<P>
75 percent of people think teens who kill teens should face
the possibility of the death penalty, a Fox News poll said.
</P>
<P>
51 percent think the parents of teens who killed other teens
should face legal responsibility, according to the Fox News poll.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a republican presidential candidate said the
entertainment industry is partly to blame for filling the young
gunmen in the Colorado school massacre with violence.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
