<HEADLINE> 3 Killed, 2 Injured in Building Collapse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Two women and an infant were killed
on Saturday when the roof of a two-story house collapsed in
northern Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Amal Hassan Rady, 18, Azza Helmy, 22 and Khaled Mohammed, 4,
were crushed to death when the incident happened in the Nile Delta
province of Qalubiya, 40 kilometers north of Cairo, a police
official said.
</P>
<P>
Two other people were injured and taken to hospital, the
official said, speaking on condition of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigation showed that a water leakage caused the
collapse.
</P>
<P>
Building collapses, common occurrences in Egypt, are generally
caused by shoddy construction materials or additions built without
permits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
