<HEADLINE> Burundi Hails Tanzania's Union Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 24 (Xinhua) -- President Pierre Buyoya of
Burundi has sent a congratulatory message to Tanzanian President
Benjamin Mkapa as Tanzania marked its Union Day Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"On the occasion of the celebration of the Union Day, we have
the honor and pleasure to extend to you, in the name of the people
of Burundi, of its government and in our proper name, our lively
and warm congratulations," a Tanzanian government statement issued
here Saturday quoted Buyoya's message as saying.
</P>
<P>
The message said that the good relations and co-operation
existing between the two brotherly countries should be enhanced
for the good of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
It said Burundi would like to take this opportunity to
reiterate its best wishes to Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania was set up on the basis of Tanganyika and Zanzibar,
which formed a union on April 24, 1964. 
</P>
