<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4 Killed, 24 Injured in Explosion in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Four people were killed and 24
others injured in an explosion in southwestern Turkey on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's Anatolia News Agency reported that the explosion
occurred at a damaged pump of a boiler in Republic Bathhouse in
Isparta province.
</P>
<P>
The injured were rushed to a hospital in Isparta for medical
treatment, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
One injured person said at the hospital that "first there was
a great sound in the bath and we thought that an earthquake had
occurred."
</P>
<P>
An investigation into the explosive incident is underway,
said the agency. 
</P>
