<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-24 18:29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Assad Meets Russian FM on Mideast Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez al-Assad
met with visiting Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov Saturday on
Mideast peace process and bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
No details of the meeting were given by the Syrian state news
agency SANA, but local observers say that the proposed visit by
Assad to Russia should be one of the topics between the two.
</P>
<P>
Upon arrival from Cairo earlier in the day, Ivanov said Russia
holds that the Middle East peace process should be resumed on all
tracks and peace in the region will not be attained without Syria.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov said that it is imperative to resume the Syrian-Israeli
negotiations from the point where it was stalled since 1996.
</P>
<P>
And those talks should be based on relevant U.N. Security
Council resolutions and in accordance with the Madrid Conference
formula as well as the principle of land for peace and the return
of the occupied Golan Heights to Syria, said the Russian minister.
</P>
<P>
Russia, as a Middle East peace process co-sponsor, attaches
great importance to the Syrian stances on international and Arab
affairs, he said, adding that such issues would top the agenda of
his talks with Syrian President Hafez al-Assad and his Syrian
counterpart Farouq al-Sharaa.
</P>
<P>
The talks will touch on ways of boosting bilateral ties as the
two countries are to celebrate the 55th anniversary of the
establishment of diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
Sharaa, who received Ivanov at the airport, expressed
satisfaction with the Russian stance.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov, on a Mideast tour, has already visited Israel, the
Palestinian territories and Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
