<HEADLINE> Several Hurt in London Car Bomb </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A suspected nail bomb exploded in
Brick Lane, east London, on Saturday evening, injuring at least
five people.
</P>
<P>
BBC quoted eyewitnesses as saying that a purple Ford Sierra car
exploded in the street just before 1800 local time (1900 GMT).
</P>
<P>
The explosion happened exactly a week after a nail bomb injured
39 people in Brixton, south London. Four racist groups have
claimed responsibility for the Brixton blast.
</P>
<P>
Emergency services were called to the scene -- which is at the
heart of a large Bangladeshi community -- and report severe damage
and at least five casualties.
</P>
<P>
Police investigators believe a man may have been delivering an
explosive device to the local community police station when it
exploded.
</P>
<P>
The car is believed to have exploded outside the Sweet and
Spicy restaurant near Brick Lane police station.
</P>
<P>
Anti-terrorist Branch officers were at the scene carrying out a
detailed investigation into the blast.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Tony Blair, after receiving a report of the
explosion in Washington, said: "These things are outrageous and we
will not tolerate them and we will make every effort to find out
those responsible and bring them to justice."  
</P>
</TEXT>
