<HEADLINE> Israel Slammed for Closing Palestinian Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Egypt on Saturday lashed out at
Israel for its decision to shut down three Palestinian offices in
East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Amr Moussa told reporters that the Israeli
government's decision to close three Palestinian offices in the
Orient House is a new act aimed at defying the Middle East peace
process and disdaining international laws.
</P>
<P>
Moussa underlined that East Jerusalem is part of the occupied
territories and the holy city's final status has not yet been
determined.
</P>
<P>
Israel occupied the traditionally Arab East Jerusalem in the
1967 Mideast war and has ever since taken measures to judaize the
city, which the Palestinians want as the capital of their future
independent state. The two sides have agreed to negotiate the
issue in the final status talks.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli cabinet decided on Thursday to shut down the
Palestinian offices in the Orient House, which has been used a
liaison office by the Palestinians since the Madrid Middle East
peace conference in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu attributed the
decision to Palestinian Minister for Jerusalem Affairs Faisal
Husseini's meeting on Wednesday with Arab and foreign diplomats
accredited to the Palestinian National Authority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
