<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Launches 3rd Biggest Sugar Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A newly-completed sugar
plant, the third biggest in Ethiopia, was inaugurated by Ethiopian
President Negasso Gidada Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Finchaa Sugar Factory has an annual capacity to produce
85,000 tons of sugar. Located at the Finchaa valley, some 350 km
west of the country's capital Addis Ababa, it will also produce
eight million liters of ethanol, a natural by-product of sugar
every year.
</P>
<P>
Negasso said at the ceremony that the new plant will
significantly contribute to the country's self-sufficiency in
sugar supply, the Ethiopian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
It took some 22 years for the detailed feasibility study and
construction work for the factory, which costs about 228 million
U.S. dollars, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The sugar factory began trial production last year. It has some
4,000 workers now on the payroll.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's other two larger sugar factories, Wenji and
Metehara, produce nearly 200,000 tons of sugar every year.
</P>
</TEXT>
