<HEADLINE> Hanover Fair Ends in Positive Business Mood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The 1999 Hanover Fair, world's
largest show of industrial technologies, wound up Saturday. The
exhibitors expressed their satisfaction with the business results
after the six-day event.
</P>
<P>
Klaus E. Goehrmann, chairman of the fair, said the attendance
had reached 300,000 as he had expected, and there was no pessimism
about the economy, at least at the fair, he said.
</P>
<P>
The fair was featured with hot innovations in industrial fields
such as factory automation, advanced robot and sensor.
</P>
<P>
A survey among some 7,500 exhibitors showed about half of them
were optimistic about their business prospects ahead. The
machinery producers especially were expecting good post-fair
business.
</P>
<P>
The exhibitors were particularly pleased with the large volume
of expert visitors, which meant those at the fair as opposed to
the general public were looking for business. 
</P>
