<HEADLINE> Earthquake Rocks Banda Aceh, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.8 on
the Richter Scale jolted Banda Aceh, Indonesia, on Sunday at 08:20
a.m. local time for three minutes, according to Antara News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
Head of the technician group of the Meteorological and
Geophysics Agency Syahnan said that the quake was the fourth to
hit the region for the past four months, after January, March and
April.
</P>
<P>
The epicentrum of the quake was at the 6.78 north latitude and
95.46 east longitude (or in northern part of Sabang, Weh island).
</P>
<P>
So far no victim and damage report is available about the
quake.
</P>
<P>
Aceh is often hit by quakes, as it is located on the island's
earthquake line, Syahnan was quoted by Antara News Agency as
saying. 
</P>
