<HEADLINE> Israel's President Visits Sino-Israeli Demonstration Farm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- President Ezer Weizman of Israel
said today that Israel and China now enjoy a warmer relationship
and he hopes their cooperation will be even more fruitful and
productive.
</P>
<P>
The president made the remark this afternoon while visiting the
Sino-Israeli demonstration farm on the outskirts of Beijing
shortly after his arrival here.
</P>
<P>
The farm, 50 kilometers southeast of Beijing, was completed in
1995 and now grows vegetables, fruits and flowers using both
Chinese and Israeli techniques, especially Israel's drip
irrigation technique.
</P>
<P>
"China is a very big country while Israel is small, but they
share much in common, including old civilization," Weizman said,
adding that technical cooperation between the two countries will
be beneficial to both sides.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the demonstration farm, China and Israel also
built an agricultural training center in 1993, where Israeli
agriculture experts impart their advanced know-how to Chinese
students.
</P>
<P>
President Weizman arrived here this afternoon for a seven-day
state visit to China at the invitation of Chinese President Jiang
Zemin. During the visit, President Weizman will also attend the
opening ceremony of the forthcoming '99 World Horticulture
Exposition in Kunming.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin will preside over a welcoming
ceremony for President Weizman tomorrow morning, and confer with
him on Sino-Israeli relations and other issues of common concern.
</P>
</TEXT>
