<DOCNO> XIE19990425.0046 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Invests Heavily in Technical Renovation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province has
effectively increased investment in technical renovation to spur
economic growth in recent years, official figures show.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu, a major economic powerhouse of the country, invested a
total of 213.5 billion yuan in technical renovation in the past
three years, or 1.39 times the combined figure for the 1991-1995
period, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
More than half of Jiangsu's 317.2 billion yuan of industrial
added-value last year was attributed to technical renovation
investment, valued at 83 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu's increased efforts in the area of technical renovation
has improved the province's economic structure, raising the
incremental value of its four pillar industries of machinery,
electronics, automobiles, and petrochemicals to 47.5 percent of
all industrial added value last year.
</P>
<P>
Technical renovation has also helped enhance cooperation with
overseas investors. Currently, more than one third of the world's
top 500 firms have established their presence in Jiangsu.
</P>
<P>
The 15,500 operational overseas-funded enterprises in Jiangsu
generated a total of 8.06 billion U.S. dollars in foreign exchange
last year, or 51.5 percent of the province's total export foreign-
exchange earnings for the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
