<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Israeli Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Israeli newspapers on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Jerusalem Post
</P>
<P>
-- Israeli Center Party leader Yitzhak Mordechai is due to
visit Amman on Sunday. Party members said the invitation had come
from Jordan's King Abdullah, and described it as good news for the
party and a snub of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
Haaretz
</P>
<P>
-- Israeli Labor Party leader Ehud Barak said that he is
considering keeping the defense ministry portfolio if he wins in
the coming elections in May.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Haaretz, Barak said that he would keep the
defense ministry portfolio for "at least two years" in order to
prevent unnecessary friction between the diplomatic and military
bureaucracies as he tries "to break through" the peace process
impasses on the Palestinian and Syrian fronts.
</P>
<P>
Yediot Aharonot
</P>
<P>
-- A light plane of an Israeli club crashed near the northern
city of Haifa on Saturday. Four people including the pilot were
killed and six other passengers were injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
