<HEADLINE> More NATO Troops to Arrive in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The NATO supreme commander Wesley
Clark said Sunday that more NATO troops will be sent to the border
areas in northern Albania.
</P>
<P>
The commander made the remark here after meeting with officials
of NATO troops stationed in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Clark, who arrived here the same day, made the second visit to
Albania within 10 days.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian news agency ATA said that Clark has no plans to
meet with Albanian leaders and military officials during his stay .
</P>
<P>
NATO, embarrassed with its failure to make Yugoslav President
Milosevic to bow after a month of extensive air strikes against
Yugoslavia, was reportedly planning to launch a ground offensive
against Serb troops in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The Apache helicopters, which the Pentagon said would become
operational in a week after arrival, will be used to attack Serb
tanks and other armored vehicles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
