<HEADLINE> China Shipping-Group Opens Asia-Europe Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The container ship Cape Race of
the China Shipping Group left the port of Tianjin this morning to
begin the first voyage on the Asia-Europe route opened by the
Group.
</P>
<P>
This is another key measure adopted by the Group after it
opened a China-Australia route last month, which marked the
Group's entry into the global container transportation market,
noted the Group's president, Li Kelin, at a celebration ceremony
at the port this morning.
</P>
<P>
Li said the Group has nine ships capable of carrying 2,000-3,
000 containers each which will make the weekly Asia-Europe run.
</P>
<P>
The route, which includes ports of Tianjin, Qingdao, Shanghai,
Hong Kong, Singapore, Rotterdam and Hamburg, also forms a network
covering the main ports of China and of Japan, the Republic of
Korea and several Southeast Asia countries, according to Li.
</P>
<P>
The China Shipping Group is a large state-run shipping
conglomerate which develops cross-regional and multinational
business. The Group has assets of 26.5 billion yuan and 390
vessels with an aggregate deadweight of 8.7 million tons, and
employs more than 40,000 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
