<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment in Nanning Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investment in this
capital of southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region has
continued to increase steadily in the past years, official figures
show.
</P>
<P>
Nanning approved 1,315 overseas-funded projects between 1992-
1998, with contracted and actual investment hitting 1.74 billion
and two billion U.S. dollars, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Over the years, Nanning has enhanced efforts to bring the
privileges of an open city and its advantages as a major
industrial city in southwest China into play, a regional official
said.
</P>
<P>
Nanning is also utilizing the Internet to spread investment
information and has established agents in the United States,
France, Australia, and Italy, he said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, it has taken effective measures to provide
the best possible services for overseas investors and eliminate
arbitrary fees, the official said.  
