<HEADLINE> Dragon Boat Race to Mark Macao's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Macao held an ever longest distance
dragon boat race Sunday to mark the forthcoming return of Macao to
China, with the winner covering the 50 kilometer sea area in 3
hours and 35 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The race, which was participated in by six local teams, started
from the Lantau Island in Hong Kong to the A-Ma Temple in the
Macao Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
Organizers said the distance was also the longest dragon boat
race in the world.
</P>
<P>
The dragon boat race, a traditional Chinese sport activity to
commemorate the Chinese patriotic poet Qu Yuan in ancient times,
has been held in spring in China for some 2,000 years.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the fine weather, the race went on quite smoothly,
said the organizers, adding that it just symbolized the smooth
transition of Macao.  
</P>
</TEXT>
