<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Attend Three-Country Meeting on Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A Myanmar delegation left here
Sunday for Thailand to attend the 4th Ministerial Meeting of
Myanmar, Thailand and Laos on cooperation in drug control due to
begin in Bangkok Monday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation was led by Colonel Thein Nyunt, minister of
Progress of Border Areas and National Races and Development
Affairs. He is also vice-chairman of the Myanmar Central Committee
for Drug Abuse Control.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting is expected to discuss cooperative measures
to counter and suppress narcotic trade and trafficking, and tackle
drug problems on the three countries' border.
</P>
<P>
In July 1997, the three agreed at their third ministerial
meeting in Vientiane to cooperate in eradicating opium poppy
cultivation in the border areas and combating trafficking of
chemicals and materials for the production of narcotic drugs.
</P>
<P>
The three countries also called for coordination among law
enforcement agencies for exchange of information on drug control
measures and enacting laws and rules on drug abuse control in the
sub-region.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar, Thailand and Laos meet in the golden triangle area
where narcotic drug production and trafficking are critical.
</P>
