<DOCNO> XIE19990425.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Institute: S.Korea GNP to Grow 4.3 Percent in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 25 (Xinhua) -- South Korea will see a 4.3 percent
economic growth for this year despite dim prospects for exports,
investments and balance of payments, the Korea Development
Institute) said.
</P>
<P>
The institute's 1999 economic forecast almost doubled the 2.2
percent growth rate predicted at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Under the adjusted prediction, the country's economic growth
will register a 2.9 percent rise in the first quarter, 4.8 percent
in the second, and 4.7 percent in the third and the fourth
quarters.
</P>
<P>
However, the surplus in balance of payments is likely to stand
at 21.3 billion U.S. dollars instead of 23.6 billion dollars as
initially projected, said the institute.
</P>
<P>
Consumer spending will jump 4.1 percent based on more income,
rise in the value of personal assets and of the South Korean won.
</P>
<P>
Investments will post an average 2.2 percent increase, 9.6
percent hike for facility investments but minus 1 percent for
construction, the institute said.
</P>
<P>
Exports will grow 2.4 percent while imports will increase 20.5
percent and inflation will hover at 2 percent, added the report.
</P>
</TEXT>
