<HEADLINE> S.Korea Allows Illegal Foreigners to Leave Without Paying Fines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 25 (Xinhua) -- South Korea will allow illegal
foreign workers to leave in May without paying fines, the Justice
Ministry said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
After May, the law enforcement authorities will take measures
to punish illegal foreign workers and their South Korean employees,
a ministry spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
More than 111,000 foreign laborers are illegally working in
South Korea and many of them cannot return to their countries
because of the millions of South Korean won in fines to the South
Korean Immigration Office.
</P>
<P>
The fines, which were originally intended to prevent foreigners
from overstaying their visas, are also preventing some illegal
foreign workers from returning home, said the spokesman. 
</P>
