<HEADLINE> 9 Tamil Rebels killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Saturday killed nine Tamil rebels in separate clashes with the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) in the north of the
country, a military spokesman announced here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Rp Witana said the troops engaged a group of LTTE
rebels with small arms on Sunday afternoon and killed five rebels
and injured four others in the north of Oddusudan in the Northern
Province.
</P>
<P>
Around 10:50 a.m. Sunday in west of Paranthan, government
troops observed a group of LTTE female cadres moving towards
Paranthan and engaged them with machine guns and small arms,
killing at least three of them, he said.
</P>
<P>
Witana added that government troops operating ahead of defenses
sniped and killed one LTTE terrorist at Paranthan on Sunday
morning.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been waging a war against the government
since 1983 for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
