<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Issues Giant Panda Stamp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong Post issued here
Sunday a "Giant Pandas in Hong Kong" stamp sheetlet to mark the
recent arrival of two giant pandas, An An and Jia Jia.
</P>
<P>
David Lan, secretary for home affairs of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, said at the issuing ceremony that the two
pandas, as a gift from the Central Government, are in the
spotlight of the media for the last two months.
</P>
<P>
The SAR government and the Ocean Park, where the pandas'
habitat is located, are "well prepared for their arrival and
arrangements were meticulously made for their conveyance and
habitat setting," he said.
</P>
<P>
The two pandas arrived here on March 11. 
</P>
</TEXT>
