<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Draws More Overseas Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China's leading industrial city
of Shanghai has approved 327 overseas-funded enterprises during
the first quarter of the year, with combined contractual overseas
investment up to 912 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
This has brought the total number of overseas-funded
enterprises in Shanghai to 18,000, and the entire volume of
contractual funds to 90 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among the newly established enterprises, 29 involve an
investment of more than 10 million U.S. dollars each, and half are
manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
Over one-third of the investors come from Europe and north
America, a slight increase from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The average size of the projects has dwindled, however, with
registered capital for each enterprise standing at 1.73 million U.
S. dollars, one million U.S. dollars less than the figure for the
previously established enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
