<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian's Economy Grows Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 25 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province has
reported a steady increase in its economic returns in the first
quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Its gross domestic product grew 10.9 percent on a yearly basis
to 64.06 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The province's industrial output value reached 48.29 billion
yuan, up 16.4 percent; the ratio of sales to products stood at 95.
62 percent, a rise of 0.84 percentage points; the investment for
fixed assets and fiscal income has also increased by big margins.
</P>
<P>
Fujian will further improve its industrial structure, upgrade
enterprise technology, invest more in fixed assets and expand
consumer and foreign trade markets this year, according to
provincial authorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
