<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe To Further Ties With China: Mugabe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China is Zimbabwe's best friend
and Zimbabwe will further its economic, cultural and political
cooperations with China toward the 21st century, President Robert
Mugabe said.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe made the remarks in an interview with Xinhua and China
Radio International in Harare Saturday before leaving for China.
</P>
<P>
He will pay a working visit to China from April 29 to May 6 at
the invitation of Chinese President Jiang Zemin and at the same
time attend the opening ceremony of the '99 China Kunming
International Horticultural Exposition on May 1.
</P>
<P>
The president said he felt greatly honored to have been invited
to attend the great and historic horticultural exposition.
</P>
<P>
On Sino-Zimbabwean relations, Mugabe said Zimbabwe and China
enjoy excellent relationship, and the ever-lasting friendly
relations between the two countries will be further consolidated
by the growing economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwean president also said that during his visit, he
will discuss with the Chinese leaders issues on bilateral trade,
economic and technical cooperations in infrastructural
construction, water conservancy, manufacturing and processing
projects as well as cultural exchanges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
