<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Key Railway to Have Double Track </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Within five years a double track
is to be added to the Lanzhou-Baoji section of the Lanzhou-
Lianyungang railway, an important transport network linking
northwest, central and east China.
</P>
<P>
Work is expected to begin in October this year, with a total
cost of 11.5 billion yuan, according to a source from the Ministry
of Railways.
</P>
<P>
The 487 kilometer Lanzhou-Baoji section is the only single
track section of the railway and is currently a troublesome
transport "bottleneck".
</P>
<P>
Once the double track is built it is expected that the section
will handle 45 million tons of goods annually, compared with only
12 million at present. It is planned that sixty pairs of trains
per day will make use of the improved section, more than five
times the number in the past.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
