<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Johnson Retains WBC Middleweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- American Keith Holmes
reclaimed the World Boxing Council middleweight title here
Saturday night, stopping Hacine Cherifi in the seventh round of a
bout that featured open scoring.
</P>
<P>
The scores were supposed to be told to the crowd and a national
television audience after the fourth and eighth rounds. Holmes
landed a barrage of punches that caused referee Frank Capuccino to
stop the fight in the seventh round.
</P>
<P>
In the first fight, which also featured open scoring, Mark
Johnson claimed the vacant International Boxing Federation junior
bantamweight title with a unanimous decision over Ratanachai
Vorapin of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
After the fourth round of the WBC bout, the announcer told the
crowd that the judges had Holmes ahead on two of three cards.
</P>
</TEXT>
