<HEADLINE> Norman, Canas Advance to Clay Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded Guillermo Canas of
Argentina reached his first career ATP Tour final Saturday when
seventh-seeded Christian Ruud retired in the first set of their
semifinal of the Clay Court Championships in Florida, the United
States.
</P>
<P>
Canas moved into the final against eighth-seeded Magnus Norman,
who cruised to a 6-2, 6-1 victory over qualifier Max Mirnyi of
Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Norman entered the tournament having won just three of nine
matches this year. He owns two career ATP Tour titles, most
recently in Amsterdam last August, and four of his five finals
have been on clay.
</P>
<P>
In doubles, Jim Courier of the United States and Australia's
Todd Woodbridge moved into the final by beating Lucas Arnold and
Mariano Hood of Argentina 7-6 (7-2), 6-4.
</P>
<P>
They will play for the championship against brothers Bob and
Mike Bryan. The Bryans reached the final on Friday with a 7-6 (9-7)
, 6-2 victory over third-seeded Lan Grant Stafford of South Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
