<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bomb Blast Kills 3, Injuring 14 in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- At least three Ugandans were
killed and 14 others injured in a fresh bomb blast which occurred
in downtown Kampala Saturday evening, a senior police officer
confirmed Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
John Kimera, a public relations officer of Ugandan Police, told
Xinhua that three were killed on the scene when the home-made bomb
went off at about 8:00 p.m. (1700 GMT) along Kafumbe-Mukasa road.
</P>
<P>
The injured were rushed to hospital and two are still in
critical conditions. The incidence took place minutes after a
security officer was shot in the same area.
</P>
<P>
Kimera said that experts including South African and U.S.
security officers combed the area after the incident to search for
possible clues.
</P>
<P>
The road will be sealed off Sunday as investigations go on, the
police officer said.
</P>
<P>
This is the fourth blast in the capital city in two weeks.
</P>
<P>
On April 11 and 12, three bombs went off, killing at least four
people and injuring dozens of others.
</P>
<P>
About 90 percent of terrorist-related explosions in Uganda
happened in the capital city. A total of 46 people have so far
died and 176 injured in bomb blasts in this east African country
since 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
