<HEADLINE> China's Steel Production on Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China witnessed growing steel
production in the first two months this year with the output
growing 9.3 percent year on year to 18.85 million tons, according
to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of rolled steel during that time amounted to 17.2
million tons, surging 16.6 percent on an annual basis, the bureau
said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, production of pig iron grew by 9.3 percent
over the same months last year to 18.99 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The period also saw a year-on-year increase of 16.8 percent in
the output of non-ferrous metals. In the first two months, the
country turned out 966,900 tons of non-ferrous metal.
</P>
<P>
During that period, the output of aluminium oxide hit 589,000
tons, up 16.5 percent on an annual basis, and that of aluminium
products hit 193,200 tons, surging 28 percent.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the production of copper products increased
by 26.4 percent over the same period last year to 155,400 tons.
</P>
