<HEADLINE> China's Output of Major Chemicals Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China's chemical industry has
maintained its growing momentum with the output of most major
products keeping on the rise in the first two months this year,
according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The production of chemical fertilizers from January to February
increased by 16.1 percent on an annual basis to 4.6 million tons,
and that of chemical pesticides surged 17.3 percent to 88,400 tons.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, 872,200 tons of chemical fiber were produced,
surging 17.5 percent, while 1.15 million tons of plastic products
were turned out, up 9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The output of ethylene grew 22.8 percent year-on-year to 690,
800 tons and that of plastic resin rose 13.9 percent to 1.2
million tons.
</P>
<P>
Production of caustic soda went up 4.7 percent to 838,300 tons,
and that of sulphuric acid surged 17.1 percent to 3.2 million tons.
</P>
