<HEADLINE> China's Output of Electrical Appliances Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The production of household
electrical appliances grew steadily in China in the first two
months this year,according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of color TV sets from January to February hit 6.9
million, soaring 42 percent over the same period last year, and
that of household refrigerators hit 1.43 million, growing 10
percent.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures offered by the bureau show that the country
produced 1.6 million air conditioners during the period,
skyrocketing 88.7 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the output of washing machines went up 11.3
percent to 2.5 million.
</P>
<P>
China has taken measures to stimulate domestic demand in a bid
to mitigate the impact of the lingering Asian financial crisis.
Its ongoing anti-smuggling drive has promoted sales of China-made
electrical products, according to market sources.
</P>
<P>
There is also a great potential in the vast rural market where
80 percent of China's 1.2 billion people live, they said.
</P>
