<HEADLINE> China Sees Rapid Growth in Telecommunications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China's telecommunications
industry has been thriving with production of major equipment
growing by a big margin in the first two months this year,
according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Production of optical communication equipment surged 49.3
percent on an annual basis to 2,138 units, and that of carrier
communication equipment edged up 3.9 percent to 856 units, the
bureau said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the output of program-controlled switchboards
soared 47.5 percent year on year to 4.4 million lines.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the country produced 3.03 million sets of
mobile communication equipment, 75.8 percent more than the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Production of computers during the time enjoyed a seven-fold
increase to a total of 281 units while that of micro-computers
surged 30.1 percent to 428,700.
</P>
<P>
Computer manufacturers in China have enjoyed a rapid growth
these years, and recent surveys show that more and more Chinese
are planning to buy their own personal computers. 
</P>
