<HEADLINE> China's Total Investment Up in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Total investment in China in the
first two months this year hit 84.5 billion yuan (10.2 billion U.S.
dollars), surging 28.3 percent year on year, according to the
National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 50.6 billion yuan (6.1 billion dollars) went to
capital construction, soaring 32.1 percent, and 12.2 billion yuan
(1.47 billion dollars) was made for technical upgrading and
transformation, up 22.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The aggregate investment in scientific research and poly-
technical services from January to February reached 193 million
yuan (23.3 million dollars), an increase of 19 percent on an
annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Investment in education, culture, health care, broadcasting and
social welfare amounted to 2.8 billion yuan (338 million dollars),
soaring 29.7 percent on a year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has put the development of science and
education high on the agenda, with a view to pacing up the
country's modernization process.
</P>
<P>
In terms of regions, Guangdong Province, the economic
powerhouse in south China, had the largest amount of investment of
16.5 billion yuan (2 billion dollars). Shanxi enjoyed the fastest
increase among other provinces and autonomous regions, with its
investment skyrocketing 452.7 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
