<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China invested more in its
service sector in the first two months this year in a bid to speed
up economic growth and improve the people's living conditions,
according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Investment in real estate, public services and consultancy
services from January to February grew by 29.6 percent to 24.9
billion yuan (3 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
At the same time, 3.5 billion yuan (422.7 million dollars) was
put in commerce and food services, material supply, marketing and
storage, skyrocketing 187.3 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
China has also significantly increased input in the primary
industry during the period, with investment amounting to 2.8
billion yuan (338 million dollars), jumping 102 percent year on
year.
</P>
<P>
The primary industry includes agriculture, forestry, animal
husbandry, fisheries and water conservancy.
</P>
<P>
In the construction sector, total investment hit 528 million
yuan (63.8 million dollars), 85.5 percent more than that of the
same 1998 period.
</P>
<P>
China has taken measures to step up infrastructure construction
in a bid to stimulate the domestic market in the face of the Asian
financial crisis.  
