destroyed a police station, two bank branch offices, electrical
facilities and telephone lines, but no human loss was reported.
</P>
<P>
An alleged ELN guerrilla member was killed and two soldiers
were injured during a conflict with government troops near Cerrito,
in the northeastern Santander Department.
</P>
<P>
Two farmers were assassinated by a group of armed men near San
Onofre village, in the northern Sucre Department, and causes of
the killings were not known.
</P>
<P>
The authorities announced they are carrying out an operation to
capture the assassins of the two men, and the media said the
assassinations were committed by paramilitary groups.
</P>
<P>
Two men and two women were killed by gunmen who shot at a
restaurant in the city of Medellin from a motorcycle.
</P>
<P>
