<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica netted in a total of
295.4 million U.S. dollars in tourism revenue in the first quarter
of the year, a 12.7 percent increase over the same period in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The country received about 216,000 foreign tourists during the
three months, up by 8.9 percent compared with the same period of
last year, according to the Costa Rican Tourism Institute.
</P>
<P>
Inflows of U.S. tourists into Costa Rica rose by 12.8 percent
and the number of Canadians visitors by 7.3 percent, the institute
said.
</P>
