The numbers of Spanish, British and French visitors shot up by
24.1 percent, 17.8 percent and 13.9 percent respectively, while
figures of German, Italian and Swiss tourists dropped by 4.9
percent, 13.6 percent and 1.5 percent during the period.
</P>
<P>
The number of visitors from Central America regions also rose
by 9.1 percent during the said quarter, the institute noted.
</P>
