<HEADLINE> Two NATO Planes Violate Bulgarian Airspace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SOFIA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Two NATO planes violated Bulgarian
airspace Friday night, the Government Information Service told the
Bulgarian Telegraph Agency.
</P>
<P>
It was probably the result of a temporary deviation from the
set course by the pilots of the two planes, according to a press
release.
</P>
<P>
The planes were 30 kilometers deep into Bulgarian airspace and
were monitored by the Bulgarian Air Defense from 1:30 a.m. to 01:
35 a.m. local time.
</P>
<P>
The planes were not more than 500 meters above the town of
Trun, west Bulgaria, when they entered Bulgarian sky. Having found
their mistakes, the two pilots made the planes climbing steeply.
Many residents of the town were awaken by the loud noise of the
engines, the press release says.
</P>
<P>
The planes left Bulgarian airspace in 4-5 minutes, heading for
the southwestern part of the border with Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
The Air Defense Command of the Bulgarian Army has notified
NATO of the violation. 
</P>
