<HEADLINE> Chinese Customers Show Preference for Home Furniture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Attracted by potentially huge
profits, enterprises from Italy, Malaysia and the United states
are all investing in the Chinese furniture market. However, they
are not achieving very good results from residential furniture, "
China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
"Foreign furniture is much more expensive because the
production cost is high," said Kang Xiaowei, marketing executive
of the Italian Vita furniture firm in China.
</P>
<P>
He said foreign enterprises spend much more on designs and
quality material, and aftersale services.
</P>
<P>
However, when it comes to buying furniture, Chinese consumer
habits are different, Kang said.
</P>
<P>
He said Chinese people are very brand-conscious when buying
clothes, food and cars. However, they do not care so much about
brand names when buying furniture.
</P>
<P>
"Most Chinese could name famous foreign brands of food, clothes,
cars and shampoos, but not of furniture," Kang said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, foreign furniture enterprises are not known
to many Chinese because they seldom spend money on TV commercials
and newspaper advertisements.
</P>
<P>
However, foreign enterprises were making good profits from
selling office furniture, mostly to mushrooming foreign
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Cao Yingchao, secretary-general of the China National Furniture
Association, said there will be about 20 million people moving
into new houses in each of the upcoming 10 years. The spending on
furniture for new bedrooms, kitchens, dining rooms and living
rooms will surpass 10 billion yuan (1.2 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
