<HEADLINE> Arsenal Takes Top Place in Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- English Premier League title
holders Arsenal, with a 6-1 away victory over Middlesbrough on
Saturday, took over top spot from Manchester United for the first
time this season.
</P>
<P>
United, who reached the European Cup final in midweek, have two
games in hand but face a difficult match at fourth-placed Leeds
United on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal took Middlesbrough apart with first-half goals from
Dutch midfielder Marc Overmars, Frenchman Nicolas Anelka and
Nigerian Nwankwo Kanu. Kanu added a superb second after the
interval after Patrick Vieira had scored the fourth.
</P>
<P>
Anelka finished off the rout with his second, a crisp shot from
the edge of the area in the 78th minute before Alun Armstrong
scored a late consolation goal for Middlesbrough, only the 15th
goal Arsenal have conceded in 34 games.
</P>
<P>
The London club are now two points clear of United, who are
also in the F.A. Cup final, on a day which saw former European Cup
winners Nottingham Forest relegated after a 2-0 defeat at Aston
Villa.
</P>
<P>
"I am very happy," said Arsenal manager Arsene Wenger after
what he called a high quality performance.
</P>
<P>
"We look to have found a good way of playing. We played at
great pace." Arsenal have four games left.
</P>
<P>
Defender Steve Bould added: "We have put ourselves where we
want to be. We know we have got to win a lot of games, possibly
all of them...Chelsea are still in it. It's still going down to
the wire."
</P>
<P>
Third-placed Chelsea, five points behind the leaders with a
game in hand, are also in action on Sunday away to Sheffield
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Charlton's hopes of premier league survival were hit hard by a
4-1 defeat by Everton who now look safe. In-form striker Kevin
Campbell scored another two crucial goals for the Liverpool side
who have spent more years in the top flight than any other club.
</P>
<P>
"Winning our last three games has lifted a bit of the gloom,"
Everton manager Walter Smith said.
</P>
<P>
The trio above Forest -- Blackburn Rovers, Charlton and
Southampton -- have 32 points. Southampton drew 0-0 at Derby
County while Blackburn were beaten 3-1 at home by Liverpool.
</P>
<P>
Charlton play Blackburn next weekend in a potentially decisive
match.
</P>
<P>
In other matches Leicester City beat Coventry City 1-0,
Wimbledon drew 1-1 against Cup finalists Newcastle 1-1 with
England captain Alan Shearer scoring Newcastle's goal, and
Tottenham Hotspur lost 2-1 at home to West Ham United. 
</P>
</TEXT>
