<HEADLINE> Spain Wins 10th Youth Soccer Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The 10th World Youth Soccer
Championship ended Saturday at the National Stadium in Lagos with
girl musician Benita treating the capacity crowd to a farewell
song shortly after Spain spanked Japan 4-0 to lift the trophy.
</P>
<P>
As the spectators swayed to Benita's rendition of "God Bless
You Till We Meet Again", fireworks were set off to bring to a
close three weeks of top-class youth soccer.
</P>
<P>
The 38,000 non-partisan spectators had their fill as the two
teams exhibited what made them qualify for the final.
</P>
<P>
In the end, the Japanese, who had lifted Asian soccer profile
with their performance at the championship, crashed to a
technically-superior Spanish side.
</P>
<P>
Spain opened the floodgate of goals in the fifth minute when
Barkero scored off an indirect freekick within the box.
</P>
<P>
Spain's pablo, who eventually became a joint top scorer with
Malian Mahamadou Dissa, increased the tally in the 14th minute
after a dribble-run in which he waltzed his way past three
defenders.
</P>
<P>
He increased his goal haul to five in the 33rd minute to give
the Europeans a 3-0 lead at halftime.
</P>
<P>
Tried as they did in the second half, the Japanese could not
hit the back of the net. The Spaniards began to celebrate when
Gabari increased the tally in the 52nd minute.
</P>
<P>
The win is Spain's first at the category after it was beaten by
Brazil at the 1985 final in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
For the Japanese, it was a first shot at the trophy, and
inexperience played a part in their defeat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
