<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 01:00 GMT April 25 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Yugoslavia would not allow any presence of armed
foreign troops on territory to enforce a possible peace agreement
in Kosovo, Belgrade's Foreign Minister Zivadin Jovanovic said in
an interview with the Washington Post published on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Such a peacekeeping force would contradict Yugoslavia's "
sovereignty and territorial integrity," and any ground invasion of
Yugoslavia would widen the conflict "beyond the borders of
Yugoslavia" and pose "dangers to the whole continent," Jovanovic
said.(Yugoslavia-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Albanian Foreign Minister Paskal Milo said Saturday
that Albania will play a role of bridge tower in a possible NATO
ground attack against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
He said that as a NATO partner country, Albania is obligated
to cooperate with NATO so it will provide every convenience for a
NATO ground offensive in Kosovo, the southern Serbian province of
Yugoslavia.(Albania-NATO)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Combat 18, a right-wing extremist group, has claimed
responsibility for a nail bomb explosion in east London which
injured at least five people on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Just after 8 pm on Saturday evening, a 999 call was made by
someone claiming to be from Combat 18 saying they carried out the
bombing," the Sky News Television quoted Metropolitan Police
sources as saying.(London-Bomb)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton, acknowledging
NATO's failure for a quick surrendering of Yugoslavia by
airstrikes, urged patience on Saturday in forcing Belgrade to
accept NATO's demands.
</P>
<P>
"In order for this strategy to succeed, we need two things:
vigorous execution and patience," Clinton told a news conference
on the second day of the three-day gathering of the NATO 50th
anniversary summit.(Clinton-NATO)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- French President Jacques Chirac on Saturday
raised legal reservations on NATO proposals to stop and search
tankers in the Adriatic carrying oil to Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
He told a news conference that stopping a ship on the high
seas would be an act of war. So what NATO navies would do if a
ship refused to submit to a search? (France-Yugoslavia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- "Stop the bombing now!" "Stop big lies!"
</P>
<P>
Thousands of demonstrators gathered outside the White House on
Saturday to condemn NATO's bombing against Yugoslavia as well as
the U.S. media's biased reports on the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Most of the protesters are Serbian-Americans from all across
the United States and some from Canada. As of nine o'clock in the
morning, crowds of demonstrators began to stream into the Lafayett
Park behind the White House.(US-Demonstration-Yugoslavia) 
