<HEADLINE> Atkinson to Retire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Ron Atkinson is to retire from
football at the end of the season after 28 years in management.
</P>
<P>
The 60-year-old Nottingham Forest manager, affectionately known
throughout the game as 'Big Ron', will call time on a glittering
career that ended with the Reds' relegation from the Premiership.
Forest's 2-0 defeat at Aston Villa confirmed what had seemed
highly likely for much of the season, even after Atkinson was
called in by the City Ground club following the departure of
previous boss Dave Bassett.
</P>
<P>
"Everything must come to an end eventually and this seems as
good a time as any," said Atkinson, the former Cambridge, West
Brom, Manchester United, Sheffield Wednesday, Aston Villa and
Coventry manager. "I've just turned 60, which is a bit of a
watershed - but age doesn't come into it." 
</P>
