<HEADLINE> NATO Deploying Tanks, Artillery in Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The NATO peacekeeping forces in
Macedonia were reinforced Saturday by 20 Leopard tanks, infantry
combat vehicles, armored personnel carriers and M109 artillery
guns.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the NATO peacekeeping forces in Macedonia,
Andrew Venus, said that the military vehicles and weapons were
moved in from Greece.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian news agency ATA quoted Venus as saying that if an
agreement is reached with Yugoslavia on the Kosovo issue, they
will enter Kosovo to carry out the agreement.
</P>
<P>
Some more military vehicles will arrive in Macedonia from
Greece next week, he said.
</P>
<P>
The NATO has 12,500 troops stationed in Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia has been opposed to any NATO ground attacks on
Yugoslavia to be launched from its soil.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian newspaper "Gazeta Shaiptare" reported that
Macedonia closed its border with Greece Friday in a bid to prevent
NATO from moving in troops and arms from the Greek port of
Selanik.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that NATO plans to send 2,000 German troops and
2,000 British troops to Macedonia. 
</P>
